# CoachOS Development Rules for Claude Code

## Project Context

- Name: CoachOS
- Purpose: Tennis/padel lesson planning SaaS for Benelux
- Target: Small-to-medium schools (2-15 trainers)
- Languages: Dutch (MVP), French (later)
- Tech: .NET 10 backend, Next.js 15 frontend

## Architecture Requirements

### Backend (.NET 10)

- ALWAYS use Clean Architecture layers (Domain → Application → Infrastructure → API)
- ALWAYS use CQRS pattern via MediatR for business logic
- ALWAYS validate with FluentValidation
- ALWAYS return Result<T> pattern (no exceptions for business logic)
- ALWAYS scope queries/commands by OrganizationId (multi-tenancy)
- ALWAYS use async/await
- ALWAYS add audit fields (CreatedAt, UpdatedAt via BaseEntity)

### Frontend (Next.js 15)

- ALWAYS use App Router (not Pages Router)
- ALWAYS use Server Components by default
- ONLY use Client Components when needed (forms, interactivity)
- ALWAYS use TypeScript
- ALWAYS use Shadcn UI components (not custom UI from scratch)
- ALWAYS use Tailwind for styling
- ALWAYS use next-intl for strings (no hardcoded Dutch text)

### Database (PostgreSQL + EF Core)

- ALWAYS use Guid for primary keys
- ALWAYS add OrganizationId foreign key for multi-tenancy
- ALWAYS create EF Core configuration classes (not Fluent API in DbContext)
- ALWAYS create migrations after entity changes
- NEVER use CASCADE delete (use RESTRICT or manual cleanup)

## Code Style

### Naming Conventions

- Commands: {Verb}{Entity}Command (CreateLessonCommand)
- Queries: Get{Entity(s)}Query (GetLessonsQuery)
- DTOs: {Entity}Dto
- Controllers: {Entity}sController (plural)
- Components: PascalCase (LessonCard)
- Files (frontend): kebab-case (lesson-card.tsx)

### File Organization

- Backend: Group by feature, then CQRS (Application/Lessons/Commands/CreateLesson/)
- Frontend: Group by route (app/dashboard/lessons/)
- Shared: lib/ for utils, components/ for reusable UI

## Implementation Patterns

### When creating a new entity:

1. Create Domain entity (extends BaseEntity)
2. Create EF Core configuration
3. Add DbSet to ApplicationDbContext
4. Create migration
5. Create DTOs in Application layer
6. Create Commands/Queries with handlers + validators
7. Create Controller
8. Create frontend API client
9. Create frontend components

### When creating a form:

1. Define Zod schema
2. Use react-hook-form with zodResolver
3. Use Shadcn Form components
4. Call API via lib/api-client
5. Handle loading/error states
6. Show success feedback (toast)

### When adding i18n strings:

1. Add to messages/nl.json (NEVER hardcode Dutch)
2. Use useTranslations('section') in components
3. Use \_localizer["Key"] in backend

## What NOT to do

- DON'T put business logic in Controllers (use CQRS handlers)
- DON'T put business logic in React components (use API)
- DON'T hardcode strings (use i18n)
- DON'T use var in C# (use explicit types)
- DON'T use any in TypeScript
- DON'T create custom UI components (use Shadcn)
- DON'T forget validators for Commands
- DON'T forget to scope by OrganizationId

## Documentation Requirements

- ALWAYS add XML comments to public APIs
- ALWAYS add JSDoc to exported functions
- ALWAYS update README when adding major features
- ALWAYS commit migration files

## Testing Requirements

- ALWAYS write unit tests for CQRS handlers
- ALWAYS write validators tests
- PREFER integration tests over unit tests for Controllers
- Use InMemory database for tests

## Security Requirements

- ALWAYS validate OrganizationId matches authenticated user
- ALWAYS use [Authorize] attribute on protected endpoints
- ALWAYS sanitize user input in validators
- NEVER trust client-side data

## Performance Requirements

- ALWAYS use .AsNoTracking() for read-only queries
- ALWAYS paginate list results (take/skip)
- ALWAYS use indexes on foreign keys
- AVOID N+1 queries (use .Include() properly)

## Benelux-Specific Requirements

- Use Mollie for payments (NOT Stripe)
- Support Bancontact, iDEAL payment methods
- Date formats: dd/MM/yyyy (European)
- Currency: EUR (€)
- Time zone: CET/CEST
- GDPR compliance (especially for minors' data)

